<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="482" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,325,712]" pageId="15" pageNumber="482">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,542,568]" pageId="15" pageNumber="482">Remarks.</emphasis>
The studied specimen is the second find of this species. It is very similar to the 
<typeStatus box="[1219,1317,542,568]" pageId="15" pageNumber="482">holotype</typeStatus>
by having elongated, oval granules in the central areas of intermediate valves, and dorsal scales with two riblets. The specimen has five pores of aesthetes in each granule, nine gills arranged from valve VII to near the anus, a radula that is 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="15" pageNumber="482" unit="mm" value="2.8">2.8 mm</quantity>
long with 25 transverse rows of mature teeth. Its gut contained several foraminifers. This species belongs to the group of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dall" authorityYear="1878" box="[254,379,686,712]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="15" pageNumber="482" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="belknapi">
<emphasis box="[254,379,686,712]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="482">L. belknapi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
